Newcastle disease [NCD], Israel
-------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 4 Apr 2015 from Dr Nadav Galon, Director, Veterinary Services and Animal Health, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, Bet Dagan, Israel.

Summary
Report type: follow-up report no 17
Date of start of the event: 22 Dec 2013
Date of confirmation of the event: 23 Dec 2013
Report date: 4 Apr 2015
Date submitted to OIE: 4 Apr 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 30 Sep 2013
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Newcastle disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (4)
Outbreak 1: Zuri'el, Acco, Hazafon [Northern district]
Date of start of the outbreak: 21 Mar 2015
Outbreak status: resolved (24 Mar 2015)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 50 000 / 1500 / 750 / 49 250 / 0
Affected population: 5-week-old broilers located in 3 pens. Characteristic ulcers in the intestine.

Outbreak 2: Bene Re'em, Rehovot, [Hamerkaz = Central district]
Date of start of the outbreak: 23 Mar 2015
Outbreak status: resolved (25 Mar 2015)
Epidemiological unit: backyard
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 3 / 3 / 3 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Backyard birds.

Outbreak 3: Goren, Acco, Hazafon [Northern district]
Date of start of the outbreak: 23 Mar 2015
Outbreak status: resolved (26 Mar 2015)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 5400 / 20 / 5380 / 0
Affected population: 81-week-old table eggs layers. Drop in lay.

Outbreak 4: Qidron, Rehovot [Hamerkaz = Central district]
Date of start of the outbreak: 23 Mar 2015
Outbreak status: resolved (25 Mar 2015)
Epidemiological unit: backyard
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 150 / 100 / 75 / 75 / 0
Affected population: ornamental pigeons

